==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from Italian ''ritandando'', present participle of ''ritardare'', meaning "to delay" or "to slow down."

===Adverb===
'''ritardando'''

# {{music}}: Gradually decelerating the tempo of a piece of music, especially at the end of the piece. Abbreviation: [[rit.]]

